-- Migration 0047: SF Wilson (aw_2711) — drop put-in lake prefix
--
-- Operator report 2026-05-22: the trace's first 30 m descends only
-- 3.2 ft (2717.6 -> 2714.4) which is within 1m-LIDAR vertical noise,
-- consistent with a small lake. The actual paddleable put-in is at the
-- lake outflow ~30 m downstream, where the channel begins a 1190 ft/mi
-- cascade to the next geom vertex. Including the lake-flat prefix in
-- the gradient calculation pulls the headline numbers down without
-- describing what a kayaker actually paddles.
--
-- Fix: move latitude_start/longitude_start to the lake-outflow
-- coordinate and strip the first geom vertex. Length recomputed via
-- haversine sum over the truncated geom (-16 m vs original).
--
-- Companion: a future levels trace --putin 45.55243198528492,-123.38959335543869
-- would produce a fresh NHD-snapped geom; this migration takes the
-- cheaper truncate path since the rest of the geom is unaffected.
-- Phase 2A (sample_reach_elevations.py) + 2B (compute_reach_gradient.py)
-- + emit_max_gradient_migration.py needs to re-run on the dev box and
-- regenerate 0046 to align max_gradient + gradient_profile with the
-- new put-in.
--
